Azure Policy cannot create or enforce Azure Budgets.

This applies to: Subscription scope, Resource Group scope and Management Group scope.

Budgets are Cost Management objects, not ARM resources, and Azure Policy cannot deploy or modify them.

Why Azure Policy cannot do this --> Azure Policy can only evaluate or deploy ARM‑managed resources.

Azure Budgets are created and managed through Cost Management APIs, Azure Portal (Cost Management) and Automation (CLI / PowerShell / REST)

Because budgets are not ARM resources, DeployIfNotExists does not work for budgets.

Implement Budget alerts: Azure Portal (Most Common)

Budgets with 80% / 100% / 120% thresholds can be created manually via the portal.

Steps (Portal):

 1. Azure Portal → Cost Management + Billing
 2. Select Cost analysis
 3. Choose Scope: Subscription & Resource Group
 4. Select Budgets → Add
 5. Set: Reset period (Monthly / Quarterly / Annual) and Budget amount
 6. Configure Alerts: 80% → Actual cost alert, 100% → Actual cost alert and 120% → Forecasted or actual alert
 7. Add email recipients or Action Group
 8. Save
